A man has denied assaulting his cousin and cutting off his hand over a protracted land dispute. Jackson Musila, 28, is alleged to have attacked his relative Wycliffe Mboya on October 17, 2017 at their Kasani village in Kakamega County using a machete. ALSO READ:

Three men caught on camera gang raping teenager jailed The accused, in his defence told Senior Resident Magistrate Erick Malesi that all prosecution witnesses who were his close relatives were biased since there is a pending land tussle. “My father has received threats to surrender the land or rot in jail,” he said. Judgement is scheduled for July 6. 